formulaTooltip.directionalHitRate:
Directional Hit Rate = directionally-correct samples ÷ resolved samples
= {correct} ÷ {n} = {value}
Measures whether the call's direction matched the realised move, regardless of σ threshold.

formulaTooltip.precision:
Precision = wins ÷ (wins + losses)
= {wins} ÷ ({wins} + {loses}) = {value}
Excludes the noise band (sub-σ moves); measures the hit rate among strong-conviction calls.

formulaTooltip.hitRate:
Hit Rate = wins ÷ (wins + losses + noise)
= {wins} ÷ {total} = {value}
Conservative variant counting sub-σ noise samples in the denominator.

formulaTooltip.sqr:
SQR = mean(excess return) ÷ stdev(excess return)
= {value}
Measures consistency of σ-normalised returns; SQR > 1.0 is excellent.

formulaTooltip.threshold:
Threshold = 1σ realised volatility
= ±{value}
Classification boundary for win/lose/noise; moves within ±σ are noise.
